ls - List files and folders in current directory
cat - Concatenate
pwd - Print Working Directory
echo - prints the text as it is
grep - find specific words within a file
find  -Used to find file among folders in a directory
cd - change directory

Shell Operators: & - Used to run commands in the background (like copy paste),
                 && - Used to join more than one command and executes in order,
                 > - Used to redirect output to the file specified, it overwrites the content if the file already exists
                 >> - Used to redirect output to the file specified, but does not overwrite the content if the file already exists
